Class RequestImpl<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.alexgilleran.icesoap.request.impl.RequestImpl<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ResultType -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Request<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ListRequestImpl, SOAP11RequestImpl

    public class RequestImpl<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>
extends Object
implements Request<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>
    Implementation of Request

    A RequestImpl, in essence, is a composition of a SOAPEnvelope for the request, a IceSoapParser for the response, and some code to to the post.

    Author:
    Alex Gilleran

        Creates a new request, automatically creating the parser.

        soapAction - The SOAP Action to pass in the HTTP header - can be null.
        resultClass - The class of the type to return from the request.
        soapFaultClass - The class of the SOAPFault that will be returned if one is encountered.

      • executeBlocking

        public ResultType executeBlocking()
                           throws SOAPException
        Description copied from interface: Request
        Executes the request on the same thread it's called on. This will not result in registered SOAPObservers being called.

        Note: Only use this method when you're already on a background thread e.g. in a service. Using this from the main U.I. thread will at best lock the screen for a while, and in newer versions of Android will result in exceptions being thrown.

        Specified by:
        executeBlocking in interface Request<ResultType,SOAPFaultType>
        Returns:
        The result of this request.
        Throws:
        SOAPException - If an exception is thrown while executing.
